          %p "then the market is dictated by the service providers"
          %p congratulations.   you win a cookie.
          %p welcome to the mobile world.
          %p (I might add, Australia is probably more open than most of the rest of the world regarding mobile services and adaptability due to the size and government regulations.  Try some of the european markets, or Japan if you want to see power)
          %p People need to understand that the cost of any device on the network is primarily borne by the service provider.  The support of the device is almost exclusively first contact with the provider.  When "Joe Average" has a problem with his phone, he doesn't ring the device manufacturer, he rings the service provider.  That's a _massive_ support burden for the service provider.
          %p
            And when the service provider tells them to contact Nokia/Siemens/Apple because their battery is flat, they end up on the 7:30 report because "Giant monopoly forced parents of disabled child to spend extra 30c on phone call. Shame, shame, shame".
